# Quarter-end retention review (QBR cycle, 4 weeks)

## Context

Across the active book of clients, run a structured quarterly business review that surfaces churn risk, upsell, and reference opportunities. Outputs: per-account next-quarter plan, three upsell targets, two reference asks, one graceful offboard.

## Outcome

By the end of this playbook, the operator has run the 5 stages below and produced the written decision artefact in the final stage.

Success criteria:

- All 5 stages have written outputs in the project record
- Each stage's decision gate was answered before advancing (yes / no in writing)
- Final stage produced the required written decision artifact
- Every methodology reference loaded cleanly via `faion get-content`

## Steps

### 1. Score Account Health

Quantify churn risk across the active book.

Tasks:
- Pull engagement, payment, and feedback signals per account
- Score every account on the 5-criteria health rubric
- Tag accounts: green / yellow / red

Outputs:
- account-health table
- scored rubric
- red/yellow watchlist

Decision gate: Advance once every active account has a current health score.

### 2. Prep QBR Decks

One deck per account, outcome-led.

Tasks:
- For every active account, build the QBR deck from the template
- Pre-fill metrics, wins, risks, and proposed next-quarter plan
- Tee up upsell or graceful-offboard for red/yellow accounts

Outputs:
- QBR decks
- per-account next-quarter plan
- upsell/offboard tee-ups

Decision gate: Advance when every active account has a tailored deck ready for delivery.

### 3. Run QBRs

Deliver the reviews and collect signal.

Tasks:
- Schedule and run a 60-min QBR per account
- Capture: renewal posture, expansion appetite, reference willingness
- Note any churn intent or red flag as it surfaces

Outputs:
- QBR meeting notes
- renewal/expansion notes
- red-flag log

Decision gate: Advance when ≥80% of active accounts have been seen this quarter.

### 4. Upsell, Reference, Offboard

Convert the signal into actions.

Tasks:
- Send 3 upsell proposals to qualified expansion accounts
- Send 2 reference-program asks to advocates
- Run 1 graceful offboard for an account that should not renew

Outputs:
- 3 upsell proposals
- 2 reference asks
- 1 offboard script run

Decision gate: Advance only when at least 5 of these 6 actions are out the door.

### 5. Quarterly Plan

Convert QBR outputs into next-quarter delivery.

Tasks:
- Refresh the per-account plan for the new quarter
- Rebalance delivery capacity around expansion vs churn-defense
- Log learnings about which signals predicted renewal vs churn

Outputs:
- next-quarter plans
- capacity plan
- signal-to-outcome learnings

Decision gate: Required output: written next-quarter plan per active account.

## Decision points

- Stage 1 (Score Account Health): Advance once every active account has a current health score.
- Stage 2 (Prep QBR Decks): Advance when every active account has a tailored deck ready for delivery.
- Stage 3 (Run QBRs): Advance when ≥80% of active accounts have been seen this quarter.
- Stage 4 (Upsell, Reference, Offboard): Advance only when at least 5 of these 6 actions are out the door.
- Stage 5 (Quarterly Plan): Required output: written next-quarter plan per active account.

